Simulating forward for 
\begin_inset Formula $t=0,1,\dots,$
\end_inset

 can now be down as:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If 
\begin_inset Formula $t>0$
\end_inset

:
 Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}^{e}=\phi\pi_{t-1}^{e}+(1-\phi)\pi_{t-1}^{\star}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Draw random number 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon_{t}\sim\mathcal{N}(0,\sigma_{\epsilon})$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{t}=\rho v_{t-1}+\epsilon_{t}$
\end_inset

 (where 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{-1}=0$
\end_inset

)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Compute 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{t}^{\star}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}^{\star}$
\end_inset

 given 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}^{e}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{t}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Run this simulation for 
\begin_inset Formula $500$
\end_inset

 periods using the seed 
\begin_inset Formula $123$
\end_inset

,
 and plot the time series of output,
 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{t}^{\star}$
\end_inset

,
 inflation,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}^{\star}$
\end_inset

,
 and the demand shock 
\begin_inset Formula $v_{t}$
\end_inset

.
 Compute the standard deviation of output,
 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{t}^{\star}$
\end_inset

,
 and inflation,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{t}^{\star}$
\end_inset

,
 and their correlation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Repeat this exercise for 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho=0.50$
\end_inset

 using the same random draws.
\end_layout

